#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Learn about the ROCmPackage helper in Spack, which provides standard "
"variants, dependencies, and conflicts for building packages that target AMD "
"GPUs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:13
msgid "ROCm"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:15
msgid ""
"The ``ROCmPackage`` is not a build system but a helper package. Like "
"``CudaPackage``, it provides standard variants, dependencies, and conflicts "
"to facilitate building packages targeting AMD GPUs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:18
msgid ""
"You can find the source for this package (and suggestions for setting up "
"your ``packages.yaml`` file) at `<https://github.com/spack/spack-packages/"
"blob/develop/repos/spack_repo/builtin/build_systems/rocm.py>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:21
msgid "Variants"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:23
msgid "This package provides the following variants:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:25
msgid "**rocm**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:27
msgid ""
"This variant is used to enable/disable building with ``rocm``. The default "
"is disabled (or ``False``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:30
msgid "**amdgpu_target**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:32
msgid ""
"This variant supports the optional specification of the AMD GPU "
"architecture. Valid values are the names of the GPUs (e.g., ``gfx701``), "
"which are maintained in the ``amdgpu_targets`` property."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:36
msgid "Dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:38
msgid ""
"This package defines basic ROCm dependencies, including ``llvm`` and ``hip``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:41
msgid "Conflicts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:43
msgid ""
"Conflicts are used to prevent builds with known bugs or issues. This package "
"already requires that the ``amdgpu_target`` always be specified for ROCm "
"builds. It also defines a conflict that prevents builds with an "
"``amdgpu_target`` when ``rocm`` is disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:47
msgid ""
"Refer to :ref:`packaging_conflicts` for more information on package "
"conflicts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:50
msgid "Methods"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:52
msgid ""
"This package provides one custom helper method, which is used to build "
"standard AMD HIP compiler flags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:54
msgid "**hip_flags**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:55
msgid ""
"This built-in static method returns the appropriately formatted ``--amdgpu-"
"target`` build option for ``hipcc``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:57
msgid ""
"This method must be explicitly called when you are creating the arguments "
"for your build in order to use the values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:60
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:62
msgid ""
"This helper package can be added to your package by adding it as a base "
"class of your package. For example, you can add it to your :ref:"
"`CMakePackage <cmakepackage>`-based package as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:65
msgid ""
"class MyRocmPackage(CMakePackage, ROCmPackage):\n"
"    ...\n"
"    # Ensure +rocm and amdgpu_targets are passed to dependencies\n"
"    depends_on(\"mydeppackage\", when=\"+rocm\")\n"
"    for val in ROCmPackage.amdgpu_targets:\n"
"        depends_on(f\"mydeppackage amdgpu_target={val}\", "
"when=f\"amdgpu_target={val}\")\n"
"    ...\n"
"\n"
"    def cmake_args(self):\n"
"        spec = self.spec\n"
"        args = []\n"
"        ...\n"
"        if spec.satisfies(\"+rocm\"):\n"
"            # Set up the HIP macros needed by the build\n"
"            args.extend([\"-DENABLE_HIP=ON\", f\"-DHIP_ROOT_DIR={spec['hip']."
"prefix}\"])\n"
"            rocm_archs = spec.variants[\"amdgpu_target\"].value\n"
"            if \"none\" not in rocm_archs:\n"
"                args.append(f\"-DHIP_HIPCC_FLAGS=--amdgpu-target={','."
"join(rocm_archs)}\")\n"
"        else:\n"
"            # Ensure build with HIP is disabled\n"
"            args.append(\"-DENABLE_HIP=OFF\")\n"
"        ...\n"
"        return args\n"
"\n"
"    ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:94
msgid ""
"assuming only the ``ENABLE_HIP``, ``HIP_ROOT_DIR``, and ``HIP_HIPCC_FLAGS`` "
"macros are required to be set and the only dependency needing ROCm options "
"is ``mydeppackage``. You will need to customize the flags as needed for your "
"build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:97
msgid ""
"This example also illustrates how to check for the ``rocm`` variant using "
"``self.spec`` and how to retrieve the ``amdgpu_target`` variant's value "
"using ``self.spec.variants[\"amdgpu_target\"].value``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/rocmpackage.rst:99
msgid ""
"All five packages using ``ROCmPackage`` as of January 2021 also use the :ref:"
"`CudaPackage <cudapackage>`. So, it is worth looking at those packages to "
"get ideas for creating a package that can support both ``cuda`` and ``rocm``."
msgstr ""
